					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">No date.</hi></p>						

						<p>The record is in Sanskrit in Grantha. Gives the relationship of king <hi rend="bold">Champaka Kēraḷa</hi> as the <hi rend="italic">dauhitra</hi> (daughter's son) of <hi rend="bold">Jayasiṁha,</hi> the son of <hi rend="bold">Gōdēśvara,</hi> the sister's son of <hi rend="bold">Kulaśēkhara</hi> and the brother of <hi rend="bold">Mārttāṇḍa,</hi> and refers to the setting up of the lamp post (<hi rend="italic">kētu-staṁbha</hi>) by him in front of Raṅgēśa (god Raṅganātha). The pillar bears at the top of the inscription, a graffito of a couchant tiger (?) with its mouth open, the right paw raised and the tail twisted. The record is not dated.</p>						

						</summary>
